title.narrative: Strengthened national capacity to develop an operational child protection system and child-friendly justice services

description.narrative: The capacity of 8,211 key officers in the welfare, health and education sectors was significantly enhanced to provide timely child protection services, alternative care, mental health and psychosocial support for children in the context of COVID-19. Technical guidelines, training programmes on case management, alternative care and mental health care in COVID-19 and emergency contexts, and child protection policies in social protection centres have been developed and implemented. UNICEF supported 11,762 vulnerable children, including orphans due to COVID, victims of abuse, children with mental health issues and child laborers, with case management, child protection services and psychosocial support. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:03/02/2022
